This paper discusses compressed bitmap indexes used in databases and search engines, which are relevant to the sub-categories of database systems (cs.DB), information retrieval (cs.IR), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC), and cryptography and security (cs.CR). However, the focus on bitmap compression techniques and their performance optimizations suggests that cs.DB and cs.IR are the most likely sub-categories.
